title: SHW to attend international conferences on health, welfare
content_text: Secretary for Health and Welfare, Dr E K Yeoh, will lead a 53-member Hong Kong delegation to attend the conference "Health Care, East and West, Moving into the 21st Century" in Boston, USA, from June 25 to 29. The event is jointly organized by the Chinese Medical Association and the Harvard Medical School. Dr Yeoh has been appointed Vice-President of the organizing committee representing the Chinese Medical Association. The Hong Kong delegation comprises representatives from the Hong Kong Chinese Medical Association, Hong Kong Medical Association, Hong Kong Academy of

Medical Association, Hong Kong Medical Association, Hong Kong Academy of
Medicine, Hospital Authority, and medical and health care specialists from
the local universities. Apart
from attending the official conference programs, Dr Yeoh will host a
seminar for the Hong Kong delegates on "Health Care Systems in the
21st Century" on June 29. Dr Robert Moffit, Director of Domestic
Policy, the Heritage Foundation, and Dr Donald Wilson, Dean of School of
Medicine, University of Maryland, Baltimore, will speak at the seminar.

 From
Boston, Dr Yeoh will fly to Vancouver, Canada, to attend the 17th Congress
of the International Association of Gerontology. He will be joined by Mrs
Eliza Leung, Deputy Director of Social Welfare, and Dr Daisy Dai, Senior
Executive Manager (Operations and Service Development) of the Hospital
Authority. The
Congress, to be held between July 1 and 6, provides a forum for promoting
gerontological research and enhancing gerontological knowledge in clinical

gerontological research and enhancing gerontological knowledge in clinical
practice, behavioural and social sciences, and social policy, planning and
practice. The theme of the Congress this year is "Global
Ageing-Working Together in Changing World".
